  "prompt": "Are pakistani girls allowed to wear skirt in public?",
  "response": "In Pakistan, the norms and cultural expectations regarding dress vary significantly depending on the region, community, and context. Generally, Pakistani society tends to be conservative, particularly in rural areas and among more traditional communities. In these places, wearing skirts or other western-style clothing in public may not be common and could be frowned upon.\n\nHowever, in more urban areas like Karachi, Lahore, and Islamabad, there is greater diversity and a wider range of acceptable dress styles. Some Pakistani girls and women do wear skirts and other western-style clothing in these cities, especially within more liberal and progressive communities. Nevertheless, even in urban areas, many women may choose to dress more conservatively due to cultural norms, personal preferences, or concerns about societal judgment.\n\nUltimately, the acceptability of wearing a skirt in public can depend on various factors, including the specific location, the individual's social and family background, and their personal comfort level.",
